author: COMSOL
description:
In this example, a heterogeneous NMC (Nickel-Manganese-Cobalt) electrode structure is generated from tomography data using a Model Method.

Time-dependent discharge and electrochemical impedance spectroscopy (EIS) simulations are then made on the full 3D geometry.

A solid mechanics simulation is also made to study the effect of electrode expansion/contraction on the particle and binder stresses.
